Package: netrankr
Type: Package
Title: A package for centrality analyses of networks
Version: 0.0.4
Author: David Schoch
Authors@R: person("David", "Schoch", , "david.schoch@uni-konstanz.de", c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: David Schoch <david.schoch@uni-konstanz.de>
Description: This package implements functions that can be used for network centrality related analyses of networks. While the package implements some indices, its main focus lies on index-free assessment of centrality. This includes probabilistic methods like expected node ranks and relative rank probabilities (how likely is it that a node is more central than another?).
URL: https://github.com/schochastics/netrankr
BugReports: https://github.com/schochastics/netrankr/issues
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: R (>= 3.0.1)
Imports: igraph (>= 1.0.1),
    Rcpp(>= 0.12.8)
LinkingTo: Rcpp,RcppArmadillo
SystemRequirements: C++11
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
